Sunday late afternoon on March 14, 2021 was my first carry out dining experience since Covid forced restaurants to shut down last year. I ordered a single order of Japanese Pan Noodles and was asked by Evans to sit and wait for my name to be called. I paid and tipped with a credit card. As I patiently waited more diners entered and placed their carry out orders. When the names of the customers who entered after me were called I approached the counter to see if my bag had been placed on the counter. Evans was taking another person’s order and when he saw me looking at the names on the bags he rudely informed me that none of the orders on the counter were mine. He then apologized to the person whose order he was taking. I did not receive an apology or explanation for his harshness that occurred in the presence of another customer. When my order was finally ready he tried to do damage control by addressing me in a pseudo-polite way but the damage had already been done. Evans has no business working with customers.

So I am a noodles and company fan, I rarely have any issues when I come. Twice now I have been extremely disappointed and dissatisfied with the customer service. Unfortunately, I deleted the photos after getting tired of seeing them. Tonight I order food, I am extremely tired pregnant and just ready to grab some food. I give them another try. This time I am missing my protein..How do you provide a meal with no protein and I paid extra it was advised again to let them try again. At this point I am tired and irritated I dont have the luxury of once again driving up there for them to fix there mistakes, I was advised to keep my food and they will send me a coupon for a free meal, so allow a third time for them to disappoint me, my to mention hey sorry you paid extrafor food and won't get the food you ordered.
